  "texts": [
    "At low but finite T, the OBD kicks in and restricts the relative angle either to 0 or π, resulting in a stripe-ordered phase with 2q-fold degeneracy.",
    "We refer to this as the Z + q AFM ⊕ Z 2 NM phase.At intermediate T and for J 2 /J 1 > 1/2, an emergent U (1) symmetry -reminiscent of the J 2 = 0 case -renders the effective spins rotationally invariant.",
    "As a result, true AFM order within the sublattices is suppressed by the Mermin-Wagner theorem [81,82], yielding a critical QLRO state.",
    "However, the spatial Z 2 symmetry governing the relative sublattice orientation remains broken, resulting in the QLRO ⊕ Z 2 NM phase, akin to the low-T regime of the J 1 -J 2 XY model.",
    "Additionally, we identify a narrow, non-critical Z 2 NM phase in the small J 2 /J 1 > 1/2 regime, situated between the QLRO ⊕ Z 2 NM and PM phases (see Fig. 1 (b)).Emergent Z q spins.-Most intriguingly, at intermediate T and lower values of J 2 /J 1 > 1/2, we uncover another non-critical phase with 2q-fold degeneracy and stripe order (see the lobe in Fig."
  ]
